{
  "texts": [
    "Firstly, although AUTOSurv achieved better performance in many cases compared to other DL models (i.e., CoxPASNet 6, OmiVAE 15, SALMON 11, with modifications made to better suit our purpose), in some cases, Surv-OmiVAE outperformed AUTOSurv.",
    "For example, in TCGA-BRCA dataset, when miRNA expression data and clinical variables were used as input, Surv-OmiVAE achieved median C-index 0.756 vs 0.738 from AUTOSurv.",
    "This implies that proper modifications to AUTOSurv allowing task-oriented feature extraction may be a good starting point to developing a more advanced model.",
    "Secondly, in this study we excluded many genes to facilitate the \"pathwaymasking\" design of KL-PMVAE (see the \"Methods\" section for more details), which could cause information loss.",
    "Improvements in the pre-filtering process will be another focus in future studies."
  ]
}